==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[dran|drān]]'' ‘male bee’, from Germanic ''*dran-''.  Cognate with dialectal German ''[[Dräne]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/drəʊn/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊn|-əʊn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[male]] [[bee]] or [[wasp]], which does not work but can fertilise the queen.
# An [[unmanned]] [[aircraft]].
# A low-pitched [[hum]] or [[buzz]].
# One of the fixed-pitch [[pipe]]s on a [[bagpipe]].

